title: Tiffany Hartwell Memorial Window Eyeglass Case
description:
Eyeglass Case developed from a detail - (attributed to) Agnes F. Northrop and Tiffany Studios, Tiffany Hartwell Memorial Window , 1917, from The Art Institute of Chicago’s collection.

The Hartwell Memorial Window,1917 is one of the most extraordinary leaded glass windows ever made by Tiffany Studios, the leading glass firm of America’s Gilded Age.   A detail from this window adorns the cover of the eyeglass case, and eyeglass cleaning cloth.

  • Dimensions: 6.5 x 2.5 x 1.5 in
  • Materials: Plastic, microfiber.
